a/phan/phan-05300/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05300/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05300/canvas/1/38539762-47db-45f9-a0b1-6f4b3d9151a3","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T20:29:22.153Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Another doubling: despite her issues and unusual behavior, Cal seemingly remains devoted to his mother, Barbara Rose. Although she has long since died, Reynolds worship his mother and feels she has been the greatest influence on his life.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05300/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1220.8846153846152,169.5649038461538,310.31971153846143,400.39903846153845"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05300/canvas/1/3f9ab04e-25c7-4288-ad57-08ba2d66c1a3","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T20:29:41.105Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This moment also comes from the real life of Barbara Hutton: “By the time they reached the reception arranged for them at the Pierre [hotel in New York], Barbara was out on her feet. Half an hour into the party she collapsed and had to be carried off to bed” (Haymann, <em>Poor Little Rich Girl</em>, 297).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05300/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:744.6706730769231,362.25,666.3461538461538,342.468